title: FSX_OPKC_KARACHI - Jinnah Intenational
description:
PAYWARE SCENERY BY MSK PRODUCTIONS:

NEW SCENERY FOR THE LARGEST HUB OF PAKISTAN AND PIA'S FLEET.
BUILT IN EARLY 1930's.

Jinnah International Airport (IATA: KHI, ICAO: OPKC) is Pakistan's largest international and domestic airport. Located in Karachi, it is named after Muhammad Ali Jinnah, the founder of Pakistan.

The airport provides secondary hub for the flag carrier, Pakistan International Airlines (PIA), Air Indus, Shaheen Air, and airblue as well as many other private airlines. The airport is equipped with aircraft engineering and overhauling facilities including the Ispahani Hangar for wide-body aircraft.[1] In 2013, over 16,065,465 passengers used Jinnah International Airport. 113,345 aircraft movements were registered. Daily more than 44,000 passengers use Jinnah International Airport.
